The paper deals with the randomness properties of graphs and hypergraphs generated by hash functions, which is a topic closely related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in analyzing the randomness properties of the hash functions. Additionally, the paper presents a construction of hash functions with small constant evaluation time and sublinear space, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses load balancing scenarios, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the randomness properties of graphs and hypergraphs, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
